  "answer": "In the *Yājñavalkya Smṛti*, Chapter 1, Yājñavalkya is enumerated (in verse 1.4) among a list of sages—Manu, Atri, Viṣṇu, Hārīta, Uśanas, Aṅgiras, Yama, Āpastamba, Saṃvarta, Kātyāyana, and Bṛhaspati—who, along with others named in verse 1.5 (Parāśara, Vyāsa, Śaṅkha, Likhita, Dakṣa, Gautama, Śātātapa, and Vasiṣṭha), \"are the promulgators of the Dharmaśāstras.\"[^1]\n\n[^1]: *Yājñavalkya Smṛti*, [paragraphs](/works/unknown-yajnavalkya-smrti-cb88d6/01/translation/#p-0f4ad0).",
